Texas Latinos Are 37.6% of Population, Census Shows

-- B y   D a v i d   M i l d e n b e r g
-- 
2011-02-17T20:40:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/texas-latinos-are-37-6-of-population-census-shows-update1-.html
The proportion of Hispanics in  Texas  rose to about 37.6 percent of the population, or 9.46
million out of 25.1 million people, according to U.S. Census
Bureau data released today in  Washington .  The state’s Hispanic population rose 41.8 percent from
2000, the 2010 Census showed. The white non-Hispanic population
grew 4.2 percent, and the black, non-Hispanic population
increased 22.1 percent, the figures show.  The state’s Asian, non-Latino population increased 71.1
percent over the past decade, the census shows.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Mildenberg in Charlotte at 
